    • Constructor Detail

      • Elevator

        Elevator​(Building building,
         int elevatorNumber,
         int capacity,
         double floorsPerSecond,
         boolean debug)
  throws java.lang.Exception
        An elevator can only be created with an existing building. A capacity and the speed have to be set.
        Parameters:
        building - The building object in which the elevator is placed
        elevatorNumber - A number identifying this elevator
        capacity - The number of persons which can be transported by this elevator
        floorsPerSecond - The speed of the elevator
        debug - The elevator will print information based on this boolean
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - The building is not instantiated correctly, if an error is thrown

    • Method Detail

      • run

        public void run()
        The main operation of the elevator/thread happens here. Steps between floors are made every few milliseconds based on the parameter waitingTime
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
        Overrides:
        run in class java.lang.Thread

      • move

        private void move()
           throws java.lang.Exception
        Move between floors and transport passengers. This function implements a state machine
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - The elevator is caught in an inconsistent state

      • updatePassengers

        private void updatePassengers​(boolean destinationReached)
        Let passengers leave and enter the elevator
        Parameters:
        destinationReached - A boolean defining whether the next destination of the elevator has been reached

      • isOccupied

        public boolean isOccupied()
        Check whether the elevator is transporting passengers or on the way to pick up passengers
        Returns:
        The elevator is currently not processing transport requests

      • gracefullyStop

        public void gracefullyStop()
        Slowly stop the elevator. When all passengers have left, the thread will be shut down
